The MSc students participate in the work of the regular seminars of the Gas Discharge or Thin Film Technology Labs. They get 1 ECTS credit point per semester in case of the regular participation and 2 points if they make a presentation.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the given course is to provide MSc students with the skills for correct argumentation and discussion about their research topic, and for the convincing presenting of their research results, as well as to deepen the knowledge of students in the field of physical experimental methods.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completion of this course, the MSc student is expected to: 1.	Be able to engage in productive discussions about his/her research topic and present convincingly his/her research results; 2.	Know the general principles of scientific oral and written presentations; 3.	Be able to compile an acceptable scientific or technical report.
